&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This Vacancy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require 1 dedicated part time individual to work within a team and to carry out a variety of driving duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The duties comprise of site collections of waste, laundry, supplies and specimen collections from local GPs/ hospitals and renal supplies to patients in South Yorkshire, North Derbyshire and Lincolnshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a department we provide non-patient transport services to Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and a number of external customers . To support the services that we provide, we have at our disposal a fleet of over 20 vehicles that range from cars to 3.5 tonne vans. In the overall structure we sit within the Facilities that provides soft facilities services to the entire organisation. Our role, and that of the Facilities, is to support/enable excellent levels of patient care and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who has good communication skills , with the ability to use their own initiative to support exceptional levels of customer service. Any applicants should have relevant experience of driving commercial vehicles and carrying out delivery duties. Applicants should be educated to GCSE grade D or above (or equivalent) and have a full clean driving licence. Licences issues after 01/1/1997 will require the following categories in addition to the standard licence – B+E, C1 and D1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
